# Security

## Secrets Management

- Never commit `.env`, API keys, or credentials
- All secrets via environment variables (`Settings` in `core/config.py`)
- `.env.example` shows variable names with placeholder values only
- Rotate keys used in local development if accidentally exposed

## Input Validation

- All request bodies validated through Pydantic schemas in `schemas/`
- Reject unexpected fields (`model_config` defaults are acceptable)
- Validate message length and content limits before provider calls (add when routes mature)

## Error Handling

- Use custom `HTTPException` subclasses (`core/exceptions.py`)
- Global handler returns generic messages — no stack traces or connection strings to clients
- Log full exceptions server-side with `logger.exception()`

## Authentication & Authorization (planned — Phase 8)

Not yet implemented. When added:

- API key or JWT validation middleware
- Key storage in database (hashed), never plaintext
- Rate limiting per key/tenant

## Provider Security

- Provider API keys loaded from env, never hardcoded
- Timeouts enforced (`TIMEOUT` setting for Ollama; extend per provider)
- TLS for all external provider calls (default for httpx/OpenAI SDKs)

## Database

- Use parameterized queries (SQLAlchemy ORM handles this)
- Least-privilege DB user for application (`ai_app`, not superuser)
- Do not enable `DB_ECHO=true` in production

## HTTP Headers

- `X-Request-ID` set for traceability (already implemented)
- Add CORS, security headers, and HTTPS termination at reverse proxy in production (Phase 18)

## Dependency Hygiene

- Pin versions in `pyproject.toml` / `uv.lock`
- Review new dependencies for license and maintenance status
